\f1\b Title: AI-Assisted Freelance Writing \'97 The $3,000/Month Side Door
\f0\b0 \
The traditional content mill is dying. Not because businesses need less content\'97they need more\'97but because the economics finally make sense for the individual writer instead of the agency middleman.\
Here's what changed: AI tools like ChatGPT, Jasper, and Claude can now handle the grunt work of research, outlining, and first drafts. What used to take 10 hours now takes 2. But most clients haven't adjusted their pricing expectations yet. They're still paying $100 for a 1,500-word article, not knowing you spent 90 minutes instead of half a day.\
This isn't about replacing human creativity. It's about reclaiming the time that corporations have been extracting from writers for decades.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 The Actual Opportunity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Businesses need content constantly. Blog posts, website copy, email newsletters, product descriptions, ad copy, LinkedIn articles, case studies. The demand has never been higher, and AI just made you 5x more efficient at delivering it.\
Skilled AI-assisted writers report earning $30\'96100 per article and even $2,000\'968,000 per month.\
That's not a fantasy number. That's 20-30 articles per month at reasonable rates.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

