\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 The Secret Nobody Tells You\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Most clients don't actually care about follower growth or engagement rates. They care about appearing professional and active. They care about not having to think about social media anymore.\
You're not selling marketing results. You're selling peace of mind and the appearance of competence.\
As long as their social media looks active, professional, and on-brand, they're happy. If you can also deliver some tangible results (inquiries, sales, followers), that's a bonus that leads to referrals.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Common Pitfalls\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Pitfall 1: Promising explosive growth
\f0\b0  Don't. You can't guarantee viral growth. Promise consistency and professionalism instead.\

\f1\b Pitfall 2: Taking on too many clients too fast
\f0\b0  Quality drops, clients notice, reviews suffer. Build gradually.\

\f1\b Pitfall 3: Not using contracts
\f0\b0  Client: "I want to cancel but keep using the content you already created for six more months." Solution: Use contract templates (find them on LegalZoom or similar). Specify what happens if they cancel.\

\f1\b Pitfall 4: Posting obvious AI captions without editing
\f0\b0  Clients can tell. Their customers can tell. Always edit for authenticity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

