\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Common Pitfalls\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Pitfall 1: Sending pure AI output
\f0\b0  AI-generated emails often sound corporate and generic. Clients (and their subscribers) notice. Always edit for personality and specificity.\

\f1\b Pitfall 2: Ignoring performance data
\f0\b0  Client: "Why are open rates at 12%?" You: "\uc0\u55358 \u56631 " Bad look. Monitor performance and adjust strategy.\

\f1\b Pitfall 3: Not managing client expectations
\f0\b0  Some clients expect every email to drive massive sales. Set realistic expectations upfront: email marketing is about building relationships and trust that lead to sales over time.\

\f1\b Pitfall 4: Letting client bottlenecks slow you down
\f0\b0  Client takes 5 days to approve every email \uc0\u8594  You can't serve other clients efficiently. Solution: Build approval turnaround time into contracts. "Emails require approval within 48 hours or proceed as drafted."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

