\f1\b Title: Self-Publishing on Amazon KDP: The $1,500/Month Library You Build
\f0\b0 \
Traditional publishing is a gatekeeping system that benefits publishers far more than authors. Amazon Kindle Direct Publishing (KDP) bypassed all of that. Now anyone can publish a book, set their own price, and earn royalties.\
With the launch of ChatGPT, AI-written e-books have seen a significant boom on Amazon. This is because writing and conceptualizing new ideas have become much easier with ChatGPT. People are using ChatGPT to write e-books on many relevant and niche topics and selling them directly on Amazon using the Kindle Direct Publishing platform.\
AI hasn't made this market\'97it's made it accessible to people who couldn't write a 30,000-word book in a reasonable timeframe before.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

