\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 What Actually Kills This\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Mistake 1: Publishing obvious AI slop
\f0\b0  Books with no editing, no personality, pure AI output. Amazon is cracking down. Readers leave scathing reviews. Don't do this.\

\f1\b Mistake 2: Choosing terrible niches
\f0\b0  Books on overly competitive topics (weight loss, make money online) or topics nobody searches for (your obscure philosophy).\

\f1\b Mistake 3: Terrible covers
\f0\b0  A bad cover means nobody clicks. Nobody clicks = no sales, regardless of content quality.\

\f1\b Mistake 4: Giving up after 2 books
\f0\b0  One or two books won't generate meaningful income. This is a volume play. You need 15-30 books to build real passive income.\

\f1\b Mistake 5: Not fact-checking AI content
\f0\b0  AI hallucinates. If your health book contains dangerous medical misinformation, you're liable. Always verify information.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Starting This Week\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Day 1
\f0\b0 : Research 10 potential book topics using Amazon search and bestseller lists. Identify 3 with good demand and manageable competition.\

\f1\b Day 2
\f0\b0 : Use ChatGPT to create detailed outlines for those 3 topics. Choose the best one to start.\

\f1\b Day 3-5
\f0\b0 : Use AI to draft the first 5 chapters (2,000-2,500 words each). Edit as you go. Add personality, examples, specific advice.\

\f1\b Day 6-7
\f0\b0 : Draft remaining chapters. Do a full edit pass. Fact-check everything. Add introduction and conclusion.\

\f1\b Week 2
\f0\b0 : Format the book. Design or commission cover. Write book description and choose keywords. Publish on Amazon KDP.\

\f1\b Week 3
\f0\b0 : Start second book while first one goes live. Repeat process.\
