\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 The Bigger Picture\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Self-publishing isn't new. What changed is that AI removed the primary barrier: time to write.\
Previously, writing a quality 25,000-word book took 2-3 months of consistent work. Now it takes 2-3 weeks. That changes the economics completely.\
You're not competing with traditional publishers or professional authors. They're serving different markets. You're serving the massive middle market of people who want practical, affordable guides to solve specific problems.\
Is this a $100K/year business for most people? No. Is it a realistic way to build $1,500-3,000/month in genuinely passive income over 12-18 months? Yes, if you're consistent and don't publish garbage.\
The difference between this and other income streams: books you publish in 2025 can still earn money in 2030 with zero additional work.\
That's not hype. That's just how royalties work.\
You're building an asset library that compounds over time. Each book is a small income stream. 30 small streams add up to real money.\
This won't replace traditional employment overnight. But it will create income that isn't tied to showing up at an office or trading hours for dollars.\
That's the entire point\'97building alternatives to wage dependence.\
Not revolutionary. Just practical and patient.\
