\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Critical Success Factors\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 1. Consistency
\f0\b0  Upload 2-3 videos per week minimum. YouTube's algorithm rewards consistency. Channels that post sporadically don't grow.\

\f1\b 2. Quality over quantity (but maintain quantity)
\f0\b0  10 mediocre videos beat 1 perfect video. But 10 terrible videos beat nothing. Find the balance: good enough quality, consistent output.\

\f1\b 3. Thumbnail and title strategy
\f0\b0  These determine whether anyone clicks. Study successful channels. A/B test different approaches.\

\f1\b 4. Watch time optimization
\f0\b0  YouTube promotes videos that keep people watching. First 30 seconds are critical. Hook viewers immediately. Don't waste time with long intros.\

\f1\b 5. Niche focus
\f0\b0  Don't make random videos. Pick a niche and serve that audience consistently. YouTube recommends your videos to viewers who watched similar content.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Common Pitfalls\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Pitfall 1: Using copyrighted content
\f0\b0  Don't steal other people's footage/music. You'll get copyright strikes. Channel gets terminated after 3 strikes. Use royalty-free content only.\

\f1\b Pitfall 2: Inconsistent posting
\f0\b0  Upload 3 videos in one week, then nothing for a month \uc0\u8594  Algorithm stops promoting your channel.\

\f1\b Pitfall 3: Poor audio quality
\f0\b0  Viewers tolerate mediocre visuals. They will NOT tolerate bad audio. Invest in decent voiceover (AI or microphone).\

\f1\b Pitfall 4: Clickbait with no delivery
\f0\b0  Misleading titles/thumbnails get clicks initially but terrible watch time. YouTube punishes this. Be compelling but honest.\

\f1\b Pitfall 5: Quitting before monetization
\f0\b0  Most people quit at 200-300 subscribers because they're not making money yet. The ones who push to 1,000 and monetize are the ones who win.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

